article.headline: Kent St. 71, UNC-Greensboro 64
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Mike Scott scored 15 points and hit two free throws with 57 seconds left to lead Kent State past UNC Greensboro 71-64 on Saturday. Rodriguez Sherman added 14 points and Haminn Quaintance had 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Golden Flashes (6-2), who shot 54 percent in their third straight win. Three days after a 41-point win over Saint Louis, Kent State opened the second half on a 9-0 run to erase a one-point deficit and take the lead for good. UNC Greensboro got within three in the final minute before Scott's free throws gave Kent State a five-point cushion. Mikko Koivisto hit six 3-pointers and scored 22 points for UNC Greensboro (3-2), which had won 32 of its last 34 non-conference home games. Kyle Hines extended the nation's longest double figure scoring streak to 55 games with 14 points and nine rebounds, while Kevin Oleksiak added 12 points for the Spartans. It was the first meeting between the teams, who combined for 36 turnovers.
